"4252665" source-id="7" source-name="scopus" source-display-name="Scopus" id-at-source="2-s2.0-85107268215" last-modified-when="2023-12-04T13:22:18.943+00:00"><api:citation-count>1</api:citation-count><api:native><api:field name="abstract" type="text" display-name="Abstract"><api:text>For a binomial random variable ξ with parameters n and b∕n, it is well known that the median equals b when b is an integer. In 1968, Jogdeo and Samuels studied the behaviour of the relative difference between P(ξ=b) and 1∕2−P(ξ&lt;b). They proved its monotonicity in n and posed a question about its monotonicity in b. This question is motivated by the solved problem proposed by Ramanujan in 1911 on the monotonicity of the same quantity but for a Poisson random variable with an integer parameter b. In the paper, we answer this question and introduce a simple way to analyse the monotonicity of similar functions.</api:text></api:field><api:field name="authors" type="person-list" display-name="Authors"><api:people><api:person><api:last-name>Dmitriev</api:last-name><api:initials>D</api:initials><api:first-names>D</api:first-names><api:separate-first-names><api:first-name>D</api:first-name></api:separate-first-names><api:addresses><api:address iso-country-code="CH"><api:line type="organisation">École Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne</api:line><api:line type="city">Lausanne</api:line><api:line type="country">Switzerland</api:line></api:address></api:addresses><api:identifiers><api:identifier scheme="scopus-author-id">57204501255</api:identifier></api:identifiers></api:person><api:person><api:links><api:link type="elements/user" id="36256" href="https://mypublications.shef.ac.uk:8091/secure-api/v6.13/users/36256"/></api:links><api:last-name>Zhukovskii</api:last-name><api:initials>M</api:initials><api:first-names>M</api:first-names><api:separate-first-names><api:first-name>M</api:first-name></api:separate-first-names><api:addresses><api:address iso-country-code="RU"><api:line type="organisatio